# a-orixe project standards

- **Keep the code clean; avoid unnecessary complexity.** Prefer simple, readable solutions. Do not add abstraction or indirection unless it is clearly needed.
- **Separate desktop and mobile:** Use the same rule as CSS — one breakpoint (48rem). In TypeScript/JS, keep wide and narrow behavior in distinct branches (e.g. `matchMedia('(min-width: 48rem)')`, `useMobileDetection().isWide`); avoid mixing desktop and mobile logic in the same code path.
- Prefer project conventions defined in **CLAUDE.md** (tech stack, style, commands).
- Follow patterns already used in the codebase; avoid introducing new styles without reason.
- Keep changes focused; one concern per commit or change set when possible.
- When adding dependencies or scripts, document them in README or CLAUDE.md.
- When adding a new section to the long page, add it at the end: register the component last in `DesktopView.vue` (and in the mobile view if applicable) so the section appears at the bottom of the scroll.
